  "text": "Niche equivalency tests as described by [CITATION_1] yielded similar results. These tests demonstrated that only L. carnosifolia and L. tragophylla (with D, P = 0.96 and with I, P = 0.44) and L. stabiana and L. etrusca (with D and I, P = 0.24) have niches that are statistically equivalent. This may be due to smaller sample sizes in both cases, a pattern noted also by [CITATION_2] . For all other comparisons, niches were not equivalent based on either D or I statistics (P < 0.05).",
